      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. I was wondering if the disruption from the war was the main driver, but do you think there were other more localized factors? Like, could specific environmental changes or shifts in local industries (like tobacco farming variations) have caused people to pack up and move to different districts within the state so quickly?",
